'I've just had twins.' She was still her usual calm self, still smiled the same way with her brows lowered and still addressed Luzhin by his surname and by the second person plural. 'My poor Luzhin,' she would say, tenderly pursing her lips, 'my poor, poor man.' And Luzhin would rub his cheek on her shoulder, and she would think vaguely that there were probably greater joys than the joys of c